Latest MRC models, especially those that use Bert [3] can even surpass human-level performance (based on EM (Exact Match) and F1 scores) on both SQuAD 1.1 [4] and SQuAD 2.0 [5], the two most widely-used MRC datasets, where each question is connected with a given reading passage. However, recent studies [6–8] indicate that IR module is a bottleneck having a significant impact on the performance of the whole system (degraded performance of MRC component due to noisy input). Hence, few works tried to improve the IR task. Chen et al. [9] propose one of the most well-known large scale question answering system, DrQA whose IR component is based on a TF-IDF retriever that uses bigrams with TF-IDF matching. Wang et al. [7] introduce \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
