In this module, temporal information is exploited from different angles to rerank retrieved candidate documents. Since the time scope information of questions is not provided explicitly, the module firstly determines candidate periods of the time scope T(Q) of a question Q. These are supposed to represent when an event mentioned in the question could occur. Each inferred candidate period is assigned a weight to indicate its importance. Then, the module contrasts the query time scope against the information derived from the document timestamp \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
